posts.name: Skye Leake
posts.cooked: That elevator rigidity would have likely been a pain point all season (no cross brace). However, the renders and CAD look great!

posts.name: alperenyurt
posts.cooked:
Yes, the supports should be stronger.

But,

We actually gave up because we were afraid of having balance problems.

posts.name: Rufus Mainwaring
posts.cooked: I like the design, but I wonder if this could work with the end effector only having ~35 degrees of motion (if that reduced complexity of considerably). If you had max angle be around your second image, and min angle around your first image. Then you’d be shooting the coral (a short distance) rather than placing it, but you could probably get that to work consistently.

posts.name: James
posts.cooked: Intake design looks sick but why didn’t you go ahead with it?

posts.name: alperenyurt
posts.cooked: the team was saying that possible balance problems could not be solved

posts.name: alperenyurt
posts.cooked: If you make this kind of setup please share it in this post. I want to see what we are missing
